<h2>Jason Matheson will emcee PACER&rsquo;s Run, Walk, Roll Against Bullying Oct. 1 in Bloomington</h2>
<p><strong>Minneapolis:</strong> PACER Center is pleased to announce that Jason Matheson, host of &ldquo;The Jason Show&rdquo; on Fox 9 and co-host of &ldquo;The Jason &amp; Alexis Show&rdquo; on MyTalk 107.1, will serve as the celebrity emcee of Friends of PACER&rsquo;s seventh annual Run, Walk, Roll Against Bullying, presented by the Minnesota Association of Professional Employees (MAPE).</p>
<p>This family-friendly eventwill take place on Saturday, Oct. 1 at Mount Normandale Lake Park in Bloomington. It will kick off National Bullying Prevention Month, which was founded by PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center in 2006.</p>
<p>Beginning at 10 a.m., participants can choose a four-mile chip-timed run or a two-mile walk or roll (for wheelchairs or strollers). The event is a unique opportunity for adults and students to help raise awareness and funds to support bullying prevention.</p>
<p>A post-race ceremony will feature speakers, live entertainment, and a variety of prizes. Family activities will be ongoing throughout the event, including a Crayola coloring station, face painting, photo booth, and the opportunity to meet 14-year-old race car driver Mandy Chick.</p>
<blockquote>
  <p><strong>What</strong>: Run, Walk, Roll Against Bullying<br />
    <strong>When</strong>: Saturday, Oct. 1, 2016 <br />
    Check-in and onsite registration begins at 9 a.m.; run and walk/roll begins at 10 a.m. <br />
    <strong>Where</strong>: Mount Normandale Lake Park, 5901 W. 84th St., Bloomington</p>
</blockquote>
  <p>Registration, which includes a complimentary T-shirt, is $20 for adults, $10 for ages 7 to 15, and free for children 6 and younger. To register, visit PACER.org/rwr.</p>
